Title: The Digital Frontier
Credit: Written by
Author: Sample Author
Draft date: 2026-04-04

===

INT. OFFICE - DAY

A cluttered workspace. Dual monitors glow with editing timelines. MAYA (30s, sharp eyes, headphones around her neck) scrolls through footage. Her colleague DEREK (40s, calm, methodical) leans against the door frame.

MAYA
We have forty-two takes of scene twelve and not a single one lines up with the script.

DEREK
Did you check the revised pages? Writers changed half the dialogue on Friday.

MAYA
I'm looking at the revised pages. The actors improvised over the revisions.

DEREK
So we're matching improv to a script that nobody followed.

MAYA
Welcome to post-production.

She pulls up a waveform on the second monitor.

MAYA (CONT'D)
At least the audio is clean. If I can get the transcription to match, the rest is just timecode math.

EXT. PARKING LOT - NIGHT

Rain patters on asphalt. Maya hurries toward her car, laptop bag slung over one shoulder. Her phone buzzes. She answers.

MAYA
Tell me you found the hard drive.

DEREK (V.O.)
Found it. And the backup. Both were in the vault the whole time.

MAYA
Of course they were.

She stops at the car, fumbles for keys.

MAYA (CONT'D)
Alright, upload everything to the project tonight. I'll run the sync first thing tomorrow.

She gets in, slams the door. Through the rain-streaked window we see her exhale.

INT. SERVER ROOM - DAY

Rows of rack-mounted servers hum. LEON (20s, hoodie, energy drink in hand) monitors a dashboard on a wall-mounted screen. Maya enters.

LEON
Your transcription jobs from last night are done. Six hours for the full feature.

MAYA
Accuracy?

LEON
Ninety-four percent on dialogue. The whispered scenes dragged it down a bit.

MAYA
Can we re-run those scenes with a larger model?

LEON
Already queued. The large-v3 model should handle the whispers. Just takes longer.

MAYA
How much longer?

LEON
Double the time. But you'll get word-level timestamps, so the mapping engine has more to work with.

Maya nods, studying the dashboard.

MAYA
Queue it. And flag any segments under ninety percent confidence so I can review them manually.

LEON
Done. I'll ping you when it finishes.

Maya turns to leave, then pauses.

MAYA
Leon -- make sure the output format has start and end times on every word. The plugin needs that for the timeline overlay.

LEON
Already in the config. You're good.

FADE OUT.
